Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @paprika{1%teaspoon}, minced onion, half the garlic, and 3/4 tsp @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4). Form into 10-12 (20-24 for 4) 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

Place meatballs on a #baking sheet{}. Bake on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

> TIP: To help prevent sticking, lightly oil the baking sheet or spray with cooking spray first.

While meatballs bake, trim and grate @cucumber{1}(trimmed and grated on largest holes of box grater) on the largest holes of a #box grater{} until you have 3 TBSP (6 TBSP for 4 servings). Halve remaining cucumber lengthwise; scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard. Thinly slice cucumber crosswise into half-moons.

Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine sliced cucumber, tomato, and as much sliced onion as you like. Stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine grated cucumber, @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, remaining garlic, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Halve @whole wheat pitas{2}(halved) crosswise; toast until warmed through and pliable. Fill pita halves with meatballs and a bit of salad. Dollop with tzatziki and drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

> TIP: Cut the meatballs in half for easier pita stuffing if desired.

Divide stuffed pitas between plates. Serve with remaining salad and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: Alternatively, serve meatballs, salad, tzatziki, and pita on a platter and let everyone assemble their own pita pockets. Serve with hot sauce and remaining lemon wedges on the side.